        "description": {
            "value": "<p>This gleaming golden sword is a <em>+2 greater striking holy cold iron longsword</em> given only to the worthiest heroes of a holy faith. It's made of a sacred, secret alloy that makes the blade both cold iron and silver. If you're unholy, you're @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 2} while holding a <em>chalice of justice</em>. You can't recover from this condition while holding the weapon.</p><hr /><p><strong>Activateâ€”Sip of Justice</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\"><strong>1</strong></span> (manipulate)</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The pommel of the weapon transmutes into the shape of a miniature chalice. You drink deep from the chalice and regain @Damage[(@item.level)[healing]]{HP} equal to the chalice's level. If you're holy, you regain double the @Damage[(2*@item.level)[healing]]{HP}, and for 1 minute, whenever you critically hit an unholy creature with the <em>chalice of justice</em>, the creature takes @Damage[2d6[persistent,spirit]] damage, and it's @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} for 1 round. The persistent spirit damage has the holy trait.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-effects.Item.Effect: Sip of Justice]</p><hr /><p><strong>Craft Requirements</strong> You're holy.</p>"
